<item>
            <title>[LU-3131] Failure on test suite sanity test_56u: &quot;/usr/bin/lfs find -stripe-index 0,1 -type f /mnt/lustre/d0.sanity/d56u&quot; wrong: found 0, expected 12</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3131</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for sarah &amp;lt;sarah@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/a02cc9b2-9ec5-11e2-975f-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/a02cc9b2-9ec5-11e2-975f-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The sub-test test_56u failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&quot;/usr/bin/lfs find -stripe-index 0,1 -type f /mnt/lustre/d0.sanity/d56u&quot; wrong: found 0, expected 12&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After upgrade from 1.8.9 to 2.4 and then add one new MDT, hit following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;== sanity test 56u: check lfs find -stripe-index works == 19:01:10 (1365213670)
mkdir 0 for /mnt/lustre/d0.sanity/d56u
mkdir 0 for /mnt/lustre/d0.sanity/d56u/dir1
mkdir 0 for /mnt/lustre/d0.sanity/d56u/dir2
mkdir 0 for /mnt/lustre/d0.sanity/d56u/dir3
error: setup_indexes: unknown obduuid: 1
error: find failed for /mnt/lustre/d0.sanity/d56u.
error: setup_indexes: unknown obduuid: 1
error: find failed for /mnt/lustre/d0.sanity/d56u.
 sanity test_56u: @@@@@@ FAIL: &quot;/usr/bin/lfs find -stripe-index 0,1 -type f /mnt/lustre/d0.sanity/d56u&quot; wrong: found 0, expected 12 
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
